<TITLE> ICC World Cup trophy unveiled in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 9 (bdnews24.com)The ICC World Cup 2011 trophy was unveiled at the Bangabandhu International Conference Center in Dhaka on Saturday, in a ceremony that launched the official countdown to the event. Haroon Lorgat, chief executive of the International Cricket Council (ICC), handed the trophy to Sharad Pawar, chairman of the central organising committee and ICC vice-president. The three co-hosts, Bangladesh, India and Sri Lanka cricket board presidents, were present on the stage. Cricketers of the Bangladesh, India and Sri Lanka national teams, local and foreign guests attended the ceremony. The great show of world cricket will kick-off in 13 months and seven days, withthe opening ceremony on February 17 2011 at Bangabandhu National Stadium in Dhaka. Dhaka will also host the opening match, at Sher-e-Bangla National Cricket Stadium on February 19, between Bangladesh and India. A total of eight matches, including two quarter finals, will be held in Bangladesh
